transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, my name is Jessie, may I get your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Jessie Randall Carter, can you pull my count up and see when my prescription will be refilled?

Speaker 1: Yeah, absolutely. Mr. Carter, what's your zip code?

Speaker 2: 24216.

Speaker 1: 24216. I have you at 4309 Randall Road in Appalachia.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Was the road named after you?

Speaker 2: No, but I think it was, but they didn't actually say that.

Speaker 1: It's just a little old coal mining town, you know what I'm saying?

Speaker 2: You could have just said yes.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you know, actually it's a railroad town because the railroad was out in front of me.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: But it worked out good anyway, didn't it?

Speaker 2: Yeah, it does. That's kind of special.

Speaker 1: All right, and the next one will be shipped on, will be charged on Feb 27, unless you need it soon.

Speaker 2: What time?

Speaker 1: February 27, it's every two months.

Speaker 2: Every two months, oh, instead of one month, okay.

Speaker 1: Oh, yeah.

Speaker 2: Can we up that from, it's 25 now, can you up it to theâ€”

Speaker 1: 40?

Speaker 2: 40 would be good.

Speaker 1: Okay. Do you want 40 every two months instead?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that'd be good. That way I'll have some back stock, you know.

Speaker 1: Sure, no problem. Let's see here.

Speaker 2: How much will 40 be?

Speaker 1: The 40 would be, that one is, the package is $149.

Speaker 2: $149?

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 2: Well, that's up substantially, ain't it?

Speaker 1: Well, you're getting...

Speaker 2: I'll get 25 now for 63, isn't it?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: How much?

Speaker 1: The 25 pill pack is $99.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. I was thinking it was 63.

Speaker 1: No, the 63 was the 10 pill.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay.

Speaker 1: So I was right on the numbers or just wrong on the packs.

Speaker 2: Right shoe, wrong foot.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's what I'm talking about.

Speaker 2: So let's see, so 25 is 99.

Speaker 1: Right, and after taxes and fees and everything, it comes out to $113.95, just so we're clear.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: And they say the next shipment's when?

Speaker 2: February 27th.

Speaker 1: 27, the end of February.

Speaker 2: End of Feb. I mean, you can place the order now if you want, but it's up to you.

Speaker 1: You let me know what you're going to do.

Speaker 2: They won't let you ship it before...

Speaker 1: At this point, they might as well because it's been about a month, so...

Speaker 2: Right, I've got 12 pills is what I've got left.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So just ship them whenever you can.

Speaker 1: Just do the 25.

Speaker 2: I ain't going to up it.

Speaker 1: I'm just going to...

Speaker 2: Stick to the 25?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Do you want me to process this today, or do you want to process it another day?

Speaker 1: If you can, that'd be fine.

Speaker 2: I think I've got that much money in the bank.

Speaker 1: I had to buy stuff from my damn oven, and they hit me the wrong thing.

Speaker 2: Oh, no.

Speaker 1: And they're supposed to be putting it back in there.

Speaker 2: You know how poor people live, I guess.

Speaker 1: I don't know.

Speaker 2: You may not.

Speaker 1: I certainly do.

Speaker 2: Well, it's just, you know, we have to worry about the check to check.

Speaker 1: You know what I'm saying?

Speaker 2: I am there with you, sir.

Speaker 1: I do.

Speaker 2: We have a MasterCard on file that ends in 9655.

Speaker 1: Should we use that card?

Speaker 2: Yes, ma'am.

Speaker 1: That'd be fine.

Speaker 2: I hope it'll go through.

Speaker 1: If it don't, I'll go ahead and put $350 in the bank.

Speaker 2: If it don't go through, you let me know somewhere or another,

Speaker 1: and I'll go put money in the bank.

Speaker 2: I may be broke, but I can come up with a few.

Speaker 1: You know what I mean?

Speaker 2: I hear you.

Speaker 1: We're the same.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Let me process it for you.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it went through.

Speaker 2: Send it as soon as you can.

Speaker 1: It'll be fine.

Speaker 2: Sure.

Speaker 1: It's in process.

Speaker 2: You should be good to go.

Speaker 1: You're good.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Did it go through?

Speaker 2: It went through.

Speaker 1: Well, you're all set.

Speaker 2: Well, I know I can't have much money left in the bank.

Speaker 1: I can't wait until payday.

Speaker 2: It ain't been about two or three days now.

Speaker 1: Gotcha.

Speaker 2: You're funny.

Speaker 1: Well, you have a good evening.

Speaker 2: Thank you for talking to me.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Thank you, Mr. Carter.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Okay.
